    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-25T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-25T19:00:00-05:00" n="778"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d778">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6581/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-25T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 25, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. Reference Nanking’s No. 7, January 22, 1 p.m., to the Department in regard to
                    reported sugar monopoly. In view of the increasing number of indications that
                    the Chinese Government is considering the creation of various kinds of
                    commercial monopolies, the Department inclines to the view that this situation
                    should be followed with care to the end that, whenever appropriate and
                    practicable, steps be taken to record with the appropriate Chinese authorities
                    the fact that such monopoly projects, if put into effect, would contravene the
                    provisions of existing treaties.</p>
                <p>Department therefore suggests that the Chargé, while avoiding action which would
                    place him or the American Government in a position of instigator, endeavor to
                    ascertain orally and informally the views in regard to this subject of his
                    principally interested colleagues and that thereafter he report to the
                    Department by telegram.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
